docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign exchanges were featured by another erratic movement in the Spanish bill, with a range of 36 points and the final price at 15.74 cents, a gain of slightly less than one-half cent over Monday. The rally was ascribed to repurchases by "shorts" who had oversold the market since the outbreak of the rebellion and were covering on a turn for the better in the situation.
